git Commands :
--------------
1. git clone :
	git clone -b branch_name url_path(https) --> in case If we have main/master branch clone --you don't need to give "-b branch name"

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. git status

$ git status
On branch main
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

Changes not staged for commit: ------> file already in git and modified in your local 
  (use "git add <file>..." to update what will be committed)
  (use "git restore <file>..." to discard changes in working directory)
        modified:   README.md

Untracked files: -------> Its new file, created in local
  (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)
        git_commands

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. git diff
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. git add file_name --> add changes of the file or new file to git from local server.
5. git add .
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. git commit -m "commit msg"
7. git push


# Later 
8. git pull
9. git checkout 
10. git checkout -b branch_name